<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bremek., Verh. Kon. Ned. Akad. Wetensch., Afd. Natuurk., Sect. 2, 48 (2): 21" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="C. H. Wright" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Virectaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Virectaria salicoides" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Virectaria salicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org, nor assessed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxon is currently known from two localities (Kribi and Ebianemeyong). The extent of occurrence of the species is estimated at less than 100 km2, and its area of occupancy is about 4 km2. The habitat is threatened by dam construction (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Memve’ele">Memve'ele</normalizedToken>
Hydro-electric dam on Ntem waterfall at Nyabesan). Based on this threat, and the continuous decline of vegetation cover in the area, extent and /or quality of habitat 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="V." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="V. salicoides" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salicoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">V. salicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here assessed as Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered EN B2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
